A hundred tables are needed said the Great Immortal Fifty of them are piled one on top of each other to make the meditation platform Once must mount it not by using one's hands or a ladder but by riding a cloud to take one's seat on it and sit motionless for the agreed number of hours Realizing that this was rather difficult he asked this question
Monks the Teacher of the Nation would like to compete with you in a way of sitting in meditation called 'revealing one's holiness on a cloud ladder'
Can any of you do that When Monkey heard this he kept silent and did not reply
Brother asked Pig why aren't you saying anything I'll be honest with you Monkey replied
I can manage all sorts of tricks like kicking the sky into a well stirring up the sea turning rivers upside down lifting mountains chasing the moon away and moving stars and constellations around
