Blue birds flew over lofty towers Under the canopies red gowns were worn
The place was set on a mountain that towered over the cosmos An immortal domain suffused with emptiness
Some plum trees were just in blossom And the hillside was covered in a blaze of color from the flowers
Dragons hid at the bottom of ravines While tigers lurked on the precipices
The pheasants seemed to be talking Tame deer came up to people
White cranes perched in cloudtopped junipers Green and red phoenixes sang to the sun
