I remember that when I was queen of Purpuria the king gave all the valuable tribute from foreign countries to the queen to look after when he had seen it
But you have no treasures here The servants wear marten hides and feed on blood I have seen no fine silks brocades gold or pearls here
All the covers and blankets are of skins and felt
