Having eaten his fill Pig braced his spirits and rose by cloud with Monkey
The king queens consorts and civil and military officials were all so astonished that they all kowtowed to the sky exclaiming They really are immortals and Buddhas come down to earth The Great Sage led Pig twenty miles due South stopped their wind and cloud and started searching for the demons' home
All he could see was a clear stream running between banks on which grew thousands of willows he had no idea where the Pure Splendor Grange might be Indeed
Endless expanses stretched out in his gaze The embankment had vanished amid willows and haze
Journey to the West When he could not find the grange the Great Sage Sun made a spell with his hands said the magic word Om and summoned the local deity who approached shivering and shaking fell to his knees and called out Great Sage the local god of Willow Bank kowtows to you Don't be afraid Monkey said I'm not going to hit you Tell me this
is there a Pure Splendor Grange on Willow Hill
